name: Optimal Snakes and Ladders
description:
# Optimal Snakes and Ladders

How fast can you win?

![Snakes and Ladders](data:image/png;base64,)

## Task

Calculate the minimum rolls needed for a player to complete a game of [Snakes and Ladders](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Snakes_and_ladders).

If a board is impossible to complete, return `-1`.

```javascript
function minimumRollsRequired(boardSize, numberOfDice, snakesAndLadders) {
  // ...
  return minRolls;
}
```

Where:

* `boardSize` represents the size of the board. The player starts at position `0`, and wins when they reach position `boardSize`.

* `numberOfDice` represents how many dice must be thrown with each roll.

* `snakesAndLadders` object represents the snakes and ladders which the player must follow if they land on them.

```javascript
const snakesAndLadders = {
  4: 32, // ladder taking player from 4 to 32
  19: 27,
  37: 59,
  79: 85,
  99: 53,// snake taking player down from 99 to 53
  73: 64,
  65: 2,
  50: 38,
  45: 21,
  31: 24,
  17: 8,
}
```

## Rules

* If a board cannot be completed, return `-1`.
* Each dice has numbers from `1` to `6`.
* The player must throw all dice on each roll.
*  `boardSize` will be a positive integer
*  `numberOfDice` will be a positive integer
*  `snakesAndLadders` will be an object
   *  The object may be empty `{}`. This represents a board without any snakes or ladders.
   *  Snakes and ladders will always start and end on unique positions.
      *  These positions will be greater than `0` and less than `boardSize`.
* If a player lands on a snake or ladder, they must go to its destination.
* You must land exactly on the `boardSize` position to finish.
  * If a roll takes you past the end position, then you remain in your current position. For example, if `boardSize` is `100` and you are on `98`; if you roll a `6` this would take you past position `100`, so you remain at `98`. 
* A snake will never take you back to position `0`

## Example

```javascript
  let minRolls = minimumRollsRequired(100, 2, {
    11: 93,
    36: 12
  });
  // minRolls will be 2
```
* The player starts at position `0`.
* They have `2` dice and roll `11`.
* They land on position `11`.
* There is a ladder from position `11` to position `93`, which they must climb.
* The next turn they roll a `7` taking them to position `100`.
* This player wins the game optimally after `2` rolls.
